<TITLE> Ex-AIGP Shahidullah gets 13 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com) - A special court Sunday sentenced former additional inspector general of police Shahidullah Khan to 13 years in prison for amassing wealth beyond his known income and concealing wealth-related information. Judge Khandaker Kamal Uzzaman of Special Judge's Court9 also fined the ex-AIGP Tk 10 lakh or one more year in jail on failure to pay the sum. Shahidullah's wife Masuda Khan received a sentence of three years and a Tk 5 lakh in fine for abetting her husband. She will to serve six more months in jail if she fails to pay the fine. The couple are currently fugitive. Their sentences will be effective from the date of their arrest or surrender. The court ordered confiscation of their assets worth Tk 1.24 crore earned through illegal means. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case against the couple on Oct 24 with Tejgaon Police Station. bdnews
